    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.50"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">50</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    Nebraska Wesleyan University 
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">F O U N D E D  1 8 8 7</hi>
                    
                    <figure> 
                        <figDesc>Nebraska Wesleyan University Seal</figDesc>
                        <p>UNIVERSITAS WESLEYANA NEBRASKA PRO CHRISTO ET ECCLESSIA MDCCCIXXXVII</p>
                    </figure>
                        
                    <hi rend="caps">LINCOLN,
                        <lb/>
                    NEBRASKA</hi> 
                        <lb/>
                    68504
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>September 29, .972<sic>1972</sic></dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>5835 Vine St.</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Lincoln, Neb. 68505</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Persons experienced in planning programs know that in spite of their best efforts, some programs fail in their purpose, and other satisfy some persons but not all critics. Occasionally however, an event exceeds the planners' greatest expectations and is outstandingly successful and memorable in every respect. Your visit to our campus last week falls into that very rare category. I have been hearing comments from students and faculty all week about how much they enjoyed hearing you speak and how much they appreciated the opportunity to hear you recite your own poetry. I myself have never seeen a Wesleyan audience so attentive and spellbound as they were last Thursday morning when you were speaking.</p> 
                
                <p>We are indeed grateful to you for giving so generously of yoruself. Your visit to the Wesleyan campus was the highlight of a very successful week-long "Arts in Nebraska" festival.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Cordially,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Lois W. Collings</signed>
                    <signed>(Mrs.) Lois W. Collings</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
